<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4a.35a.14.15.001" />
<fw type="curatorial">14</fw>
<note type="curatorial"></note>

<opener>
<dateline>April 27, 1971
</dateline>
<salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt,</salute>
</opener>

<p>Tonight you brought a lump to my throat. Your words were so simple - yet so great, aside so beautiful. "Men are just mean, we are all the same, we should respect each others wisdom, each others cultures."</p>
<p>Indeed if all mankind lived by these words, the world would be a beautiful place in which to live.</p>
<p>Thank you for being on the Dick Cavett Show - and you have reminded me to try to live better tomorrow than I did today.</p>
<p>Many thanks for your stimulaly letter, It was very kind of you to write me + I want to thank you sincerely.</p>

<closer>
<salute></salute>
<signed>Mrs. C. Ward
17013 E. Holton St.
West Covina, Calif 91791</signed>
<note><gap reason ="cutoff"/>

Ans'd 5/30/71

Mr. John G. Neihardt
% The Dick Cavett Show
ABC TV New York 
New York

AIR MAIL
AIR MAIL</note>
</closer>

